value.title: Fact check: Letter thanking President Trump was not written by Rush Limbaugh
value.excerpt: Social media users have been sharing a letter online attributed to conservative radio personality Rush Limbaugh that thanks former President Donald J. Trump for the past four years.

value.title: Angel dad slams Joe Biden's immigration orders: 'Insanity on steroids'
value.excerpt: A California father, whose son was killed in a car accident with an illegal immigrant slammed President Joe Biden’s move to halt deportations of undocumented migrants on Friday, calling the administration's actions “insanity on steroids.”

value.title: Biden administration’s CBP revives ‘catch and release’ policy at border amid COVID concerns
value.excerpt: A perfect storm of events has the Biden administration’s Customs and Border Protection on its heels in parts of Texas.

value.title: Pence will be ‘very active’ in 2022 elections amid new partnerships with conservative groups: ex-VP's adviser
value.excerpt: Pence announced he is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished fellow and is also entering into a partnership with the conservative Young America’s Foundation.

value.title: Biden flying to Delaware despite CDC warnings to avoid travel
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to travel to Delaware this weekend, in what will be his first out-of-town trip since taking office, despite warnings from the Centers of Disease Control and Prevention to avoid travel.

value.title: Biden set to accept more refugees after years of Trump restrictions
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden said on Thursday he plans to raise annual refugee admissions to 125,000 in the coming fiscal year, a more than eight-fold increase after former President Donald Trump slashed levels to historic lows.

value.title: Live Updates: Biden to Speak on Economy Hours After Senate Approves Relief Package
value.excerpt: President Biden and Vice President Harris plan to meet with House Democratic leaders Friday morning to discuss the stimulus package. The Senate approved Mr. Biden’s plan but knocked out the $15 minimum wage.

value.title: 'America is back' - Biden touts muscular foreign policy in first diplomatic speech
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden on Thursday promised a new era after the scattershot foreign policy of his predecessor, Donald Trump, declaring "America is back" on the global stage in his first diplomatic address as president.

value.title: Congressional Democrats propose up to $50,000 in debt cancelation, Biden not sold
value.excerpt: Congressional Democrats renewed calls Thursday for President Joe Biden to cancel up to $50,000 in federal student loans per individual.

value.title: Sen. Ben Sasse slams Nebraska GOP committee’s plans to censure him for criticizing Trump
value.excerpt: Sasse is the latest Republican to face censure or the threat of it from a state or local GOP for not supporting Trump.

value.title: Biden to call for protecting LGBTQ rights globally in memo
value.excerpt: It reflects his deep commitment to these issues both here in the United States and everywhere around the world," national security adviser Jake Sullivan said.

value.title: Chief of staff: White House hopes to revive Trump plan to mail masks to Americans
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is hoping to resurrect a proposal from the Trump administration to mail face masks to every American in an attempt to stop the spread of Covid-19, White House chief of staff Ron Klain said Thursday.

value.title: Pompeo on Biden declaring 'America is back': 'Back to when ISIS controlled a caliphate'?
value.excerpt: Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo reacted Thursday to President Biden's declaration that "America is back" by asking if the commander-in-chief meant "back to when ISIS controlled a caliphate in Syria that was the size of Britain."

value.title: Pence reveals his post-White House plans
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished fellow, according to three people familiar with the matter. The move comes a day after the former vice president launched his transition office and announced plans to relocate to his home state of Indiana this summer.

value.title: ‘We’ve learned to love the guy:’ How Biden charmed the left
